The paper discusses feature selection techniques and their impact on cancer classification using gene expression profiles. This topic falls under the broad category of machine learning and data mining, which is covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Given the focus on classification and feature selection, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category, as it covers topics related to intelligent systems and decision-making. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is another possible sub-category, as it covers computational methods for scientific and engineering applications. cs.DB (Databases) is relevant because gene expression data is often stored in databases and requires efficient retrieval and analysis. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category, as it covers topics related to neural networks and evolutionary algorithms, which are sometimes used for feature selection and classification.
